queue

Interface Executor<T extends java.io.Serializable>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of elements held in this queue that implements the Serializable interface.

    public interface Executor<T extends java.io.Serializable>
    When the ExecutionEngine execute the process, it wants implementation of this interface. It calls this execute method. So implementer of this interface can get the calls from the engine thread in given cycle as the availability of items in the queue.
    See Also:
    ExecutionEngine

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void execute(T t)
      This method will be call by the ExecutionEngine in the given cycle as availability of items in the queue.
